ANC President Cyril Ramaphosa will deliver the closing address at the conclusion of ANC National Executive Committee (NEC) Lekgotla currently underway at St. Georges Hotel, Irene, Tshwane. JOHANNESBURG - ANC president, Cyril Ramaphosa will deliver closing address following the ANC National Executive Committee (NEC) Lekgotla. The NEC met on the weekend at St. Georges Hotel in Irene, Tshwane to discuss the state of affairs in the party and in government. Ramaphosa is expected to brief the media on some of the resolutions the NEC took.